Created by: Four musketeers s.r.o.
License: Apache 2.0

== Features ==

- Google Consent Mode v2 integration (setDefaultConsentState on page load)
- Supports both Scenario ID (dynamic, recommended) and direct CCID (static) modes
- Configurable wait_for_update timeout for consent resolution
- ads_data_redaction and url_passthrough support
- 10 custom fields for dynamic scenario targeting
- SDK handles consent updates natively (gtag consent update) — no extra triggers needed for GCM
- Works with the companion Waulter GTM scaffold (variables + triggers for non-Google tag control)

== How it works ==

1. Template fires on Consent Initialization — All Pages trigger
2. Sets default consent: all denied, security_storage granted
3. Sets WaulterConfig on window with your Scenario ID / CCID
4. Injects the Waulter SDK from cdn.waulter.cz
5. SDK loads config from server, renders banner, handles consent updates via gtag()
6. Google-native tags (GA4, Google Ads) respond to GCM automatically
7. Non-Google tags use the companion scaffold triggers for consent gating

== Pro Tips ==

- Always use Consent Initialization trigger, NOT All Pages — this ensures defaults are set before any tag fires
- Use Scenario ID (SC00xxx) instead of CCID for flexibility — scenarios can switch configs dynamically
- The SDK resolves stored consent within the wait_for_update window (500ms default) — returning visitors get instant consent without seeing the banner
- For Facebook Pixel, Microsoft Clarity, Hotjar: import the companion scaffold JSON and use the pre-built consent triggers
- Custom fields let you pass page context (user type, tier, page category) to Waulter scenario rules — configure rules at my.waulter.eu/b2b/scenarios/
- If banner icons look broken, add Material Icons CSS to your site manually: <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons">
- Debug mode: open browser console and look for "Waulter CMP:" log messages

